[SN]TITLE[SN]
Biker dead after hitting sign named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 22-year-old motorbike rider who died after crashing into a roundabout sign in Stirling has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ross McArthur, from nearby Whins of Milton, sustained serious injuries when his Kawasaki motorcycle hit a fixed road sign on Monday night.
His bike hit the sign at a junction on Muirton Road, within Springkerse retail park, at about 22:30.
He was taken to the Southern General Hospital in Glasgow where he later died.
Inquiries into the full circumstances surrounding this incident are ongoing, police said.
